{"title_page": "Chandrakauns", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox raga\n| name          = Chandrakauns\n| image_name    =\n| image_alt     =\n| thaat         =\n| type          = Audava\n| time          = Late night, 12\u20133<ref name=\"Bor\" />\n| season        =\n| arohana       = S {{underline|G}} M {{underline|D}} N \u1e60<ref name=\"Bor\" />\n| avarohana     = \u1e60 N {{underline|D}} M {{underline|G}} S<ref name=\"Bor\" />\n| vadi          =\n| samavadi      =\n| pakad         =\n| chalan        =\n| synonym       = Chandrakosh<ref name=\"Bor\" />\n| equivalent    =\n| similar       = {{ubl|[[Malkauns]]<ref name=\"Bor\" />|[[Hindolam]]<ref name=\"mani\" />}}\n}}\n{{Hindustani Classical Music}} \n'''Chandrakauns''' is a [[raga]] in [[Hindustani classical music]].<ref name=\"Bor\">{{cite book |last1=Bor |first1=Joep |last2=Rao |first2=Suvarnalata |title=The Raga Guide: A Survey of 74 Hindustani Ragas |date=1999 |publisher=Nimbus Records with Rotterdam Conservatory of Music |isbn=9780954397609 |page=54 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jCnoMgEACAAJ |language=en}}</ref> It is also used in tail pieces and lighter presentations of [[Carnatic music]].<ref name=\"mani\">{{cite news |last1=Mani |first1=Charulatha |title=Of love and longing |url=https://www.thehindu.com/features/friday-review/music/of-love-and-longing/article5329771.ece |accessdate=29 August 2018 |work=The Hindu|date=8 November 2013 |language=en-IN}}</ref>\n\n== Film Songs ==\n=== Language:[[Tamil language|Tamil]] ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Song\n!Movie\n!Composer\n!Singer\n|-\n|Maalai Pozhuthin Mayakkathile\n|[[Bhagyalakshmi (film)|Bhagyalakshmi]]\n|[[Viswanathan-Ramamoorthy]]\n|[[P. Susheela]]\n|-\n|Velli Salangaigal\n|[[Kaadhal Oviyam]]\n|[[Ilaiyaraaja]]\n|[[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam]]\n|-\n|Padavanthatho Gaanam\n|[[Ilamai Kaalangal]]\n|[[Ilaiyaraaja]]\n|[[K. J. Yesudas]], [[P. Susheela]]\n|-\n|Azhagu Malaraada\n|[[Vaidehi Kathirunthal]]\n|[[Ilaiyaraaja]]\n|[[S. Janaki]],